Privacy Policy
Last Updated: February 2026

Welcome to Pal 24/7 UK (the "App"). We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring your personal data is handled securely and transparently in accordance with the UK GDPR and Google Play Store policies.

1. Information We Collect
We collect information only to provide and improve our services. Most data is stored locally on your device.

Personal Data: Names or contact details provided voluntarily when you contact our support team.

Usage Data: Anonymized statistics on app interactions and device identifiers (such as Android Advertising ID) used for app performance and advertising.

2. How We Use Your Data
We use your information for the following purposes:

App Functionality: To manage your checklists, reminders, and address book.

Advertising & Analytics: To deliver relevant advertisements and analyze app performance via Google AdMob.

Security: To prevent fraud and ensure a safe environment for all users.

3. Advertising (Google AdMob)
This app uses Google AdMob to serve advertisements. AdMob may automatically collect and share the following data for advertising and analytics purposes:

Approximate location (IP-based).

Device identifiers (Advertising ID).

App interaction data.

Users in the UK/EEA: We use a Google-certified Consent Management Platform (CMP) to obtain your permission for data processing in accordance with legal requirements.

4. Data Security and Retention
Local Storage: Your personal lists and reminders remain on your device.

Encryption: Any data transmitted off-device is secured using industry-standard encryption (HTTPS/TLS).

Retention: We only retain support-related personal data for as long as necessary to fulfill your request or meet legal obligations.

5. Your Rights
Under the UK GDPR, you have the right to access, correct, or request the deletion of your data. You can also opt out of personalized advertising at any time through your Android device settings (Settings > Google > Ads).

